    "body": "Oh, so it's not really CORS but CSP. I.e. it's not our server not issuing a CORS header and blocking a file this way. It's rather their own server attaching a CSP header that tells the browser that they do not want any JS scripts to connect to other places (`connect-src 'self'`). So basically they would have to reconfigure their app to allow fetching files from us.",
